# TypeScript Rules

- Strict mode is ON — tsconfig has "strict": true
- Never use `any`. Use `unknown` if type is truly unknown, then narrow with guards
- Always define interfaces for component props — name them `[ComponentName]Props`
- Always define return types for functions that return non-trivial values
- Use `type` for unions/intersections, `interface` for object shapes
- API response types live in frontend/src/types/index.ts — always import from there
- Use optional chaining `?.` and nullish coalescing `??` instead of manual null checks
- Enums are forbidden — use const objects with `as const` instead
- All async functions must have try/catch blocks
